    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10–1044:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-10T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 10, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4109. For Department only. At Board of Directors meeting October 9, SKF
                    officially decided to stop all exports to Germany and satellite countries of
                    ball and roller bearings and parts thereof and of ball-bearing machinery as from
                    October 12.</p>
                <p>The company’s minutes will record (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) that SKF is doing
                    this in the assumption that the 5 points set forth in the memorandum which was
                    handed Waring on October 7 (Legation’s 4097, October 9, 7 p.m.) will be given
                    sympathetic consideration by the British and American Governments; (<hi
                        rend="italic">b</hi>) that SKF does not request an answer now but reserves
                    the right to receive clarification at a later date and (<hi rend="italic"
                    >c</hi>) that it was agreed that no publicity shall take place.</p>
                <pb facs="0658" n="648" xml:id="pg_648"/>
                <p>My 1250, October 10, 6 p.m. repeats this to London, for the Ambassador only.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
